{
  "texts": [
    "Similar to previous ANI models, ANI-1xnr predicts energies based solely upon the atomic positions and element types.",
    "Therefore, unlike more complex MLIPs, for example, SpookyNet 16 and AIMNet 68, the ANI-1xnr-predicted energies do not explicitly depend on the charge or spin multiplicity.",
    "Thus, similar to ReaxFF, ANI-1xnr predicts only the ground-state energy, regardless of whether the lowest-energy electronic state corresponds to a radical or an ion.",
    "The ANI-1xnr model was trained using both energy and force terms in the loss function as described in previous work 69.",
    "During training, we employ early stopping to prevent overfitting with learning rate annealing to ensure a high-fidelity fit."
  ]
}